3c804381-0bb2-4b6b-bcb5-b8a596d19195.do_description: To make the output, you have to... resize the output grid to be double the width and height of the input grid. Then, copy and paste each colored square in the input grid 4 times -- once in each "quadrant" (if, in the input, the square is in the uppermost and leftmost corner, then it should be in the uppermost and leftmost corner in the output, as well as in the uppermost and leftmost corner of each "quadrant"). Then, for every single colored square, do the following: put a light blue square on each adjacent corner, forming a cross with 4 light-blue squares and the colored square in the middle.
3c804381-0bb2-4b6b-bcb5-b8a596d19195.grid_description: The output grid size... is double the height and width of the input grid.
3c804381-0bb2-4b6b-bcb5-b8a596d19195.see_description: In the input, you should see... 1 or 2 squares filled in with the same color on a black background.

87573c00-c468-4872-9162-67da9a28533f.do_description: To make the output, you have to... copy the input. Then, resize the output grid to be double the width and height. Then, copy the upper-left quadrant of your output grid (which is the same as the input grid) and paste it once in each quadrant of the output grid. You should have 4x as many colored squares in the output as in the input. Then, for each colored square in the output, do the following: add a light blue square 1 above and to the left, 1 above and to the right, 1 below and to the left, 1 below and to the right. Each light blue square should be diagonally touching the colored square, forming an X with the colored square in the center. Some of the X's might overlap or go off the screen. That is okay.
87573c00-c468-4872-9162-67da9a28533f.grid_description: The output grid size... is double the height and width of the input grid
87573c00-c468-4872-9162-67da9a28533f.see_description: In the input, you should see... a few colored squares on a black background

f8a34a8c-feca-48b4-b042-d9b875051b05.do_description: To make the output, you have to...copy and paste the original input into each quadrant of the output (top left, top right, bottom left, bottom right). Then, on the second row down from the top, make it a horizontal light blue line that goes across the entire width, it should be 8 wide by 1 long.From the top right corner, go to the third down and color that square light blue. From the top left corner, go to the fourth square down and color that square light blue.Then do another 8x1 horizontal light blue line below the last square you colored.
f8a34a8c-feca-48b4-b042-d9b875051b05.see_description: In the input, you should see...black squares and pink squares
